§ 7. turris The moveable tower (t. ambulatoria) of later times is described by Vegetius‚ 1v. 17, as 30 to 50 feet square, and so high as to overtop, not the walls only, but the towers of the besieged city. It 'was covered with raw hides to be screened from fire, and was moved along on rollers to the point of attack. In the lowest story was contained a battering ram, in the middle was a drawbridge, which might suddenly be lowered and secured with grappling irons to the walls for a boarding party, while the higher stories were filled with men who poured a shower of missiles of every kind upon the enemy.
